Police cordon off a street near the scene of a shooting in New York, the United States, on Oct. 12, 2019. Four people were killed and three others injured in a shooting in New York's Brooklyn borough on early Saturday, according to the police. (Xinhua)Â Four people were killed and three others injured in a shooting in New York's Brooklyn borough on early Saturday, according to the police.The shooting took place in an illegal gambling site inside a three-floor building in Crown Heights shortly before 7 a.m. (1100 GMT). Four men were pronounced dead at the scene. Another two men and a woman were shot and taken to an area hospital, police said.The incident apparently stemmed from a dispute, and there's no evidence that it's gang-related, police said. At least 15 shots were fired and two guns were recovered from the scene.The block where the building is situated was cordoned off by crime-scene tapes. Police and investigators could be seen walking in and out of the site.No arrests have been made and investigation is underway. 
